::Q::Which transaction code creates a sales order? {
  =VA01
  ~VA03
  ~VL01N
  ~VF01
}

::Q::Which tables store the sales order header and items? {
  ~LIKP / LIPS
  =VBAK / VBAP
  ~VBRK / VBRP
  ~BKPF / BSEG
}

::Q::Which transaction code creates the outbound delivery? {
  ~VA02
  =VL01N
  ~VF01
  ~VA01
}

::Q::Which movement type does goods issue post? {
  ~101
  ~261
  =601
  ~641
}

::Q::What is the inventory effect of posting goods issue? {
  ~It increases inventory
  =It reduces inventory
  ~It has no inventory effect
  ~It only reserves inventory
}

::Q::Which transaction code creates the billing invoice? {
  =VF01
  ~VL01N
  ~VA01
  ~VA02
}

::Q::When billing passes revenue to Financial Accounting, which tables hold the resulting FI document? {
  ~VBRK / VBRP
  ~VBAK / VBAP
  ~LIKP / LIPS
  =BKPF / BSEG
}

::Q::The outbound delivery (VL01N) triggers picking and goods issue. {TRUE}

::Q::The sales order header is stored in table LIKP. {FALSE}

::Q::List the three Order-to-Cash documents in sequence with their create tcodes. {=Sales order (VA01), outbound delivery (VL01N), billing (VF01).}
